				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">- New commands for consent:
<br />

<br />
/consent group -- flags your current corpses so they can be dragged by all of your current group members
<br />

<br />
/consent raid -- flags your current corpses so they can be dragged by anyone in your raid (including people who join the raid later)
<br />

<br />
/consent guild -- flags your current corpses so they can be dragged by anyone in your guild
<br />

<br />
/deny group -- removes the flag
<br />

<br />
/deny raid -- removes the flag
<br />

<br />
/deny guild -- removes the flag
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I'd like to see this get taken one step further, and have an &quot;/autoconsent group/raid/guild&quot; command. Just make it so it can be toggled on and off. When you die, anyone in the group/raid/guild can just drag you right away, without having to wait for you to finish zoning into wherever you're bound and then type in consent. It would certainly help deal with some of the people that take forever to consent after death.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
